				<div class="postright">
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>Re: Denis:</p><div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>1. ... the connect has at least the magic id to detect protocol changes. next version could be 0x0001041727101980 instead of 0x0000041727101980.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>+1.&#160; This is better then relying on a datagram length change to signal an update to something with versioning and limited extension capability (reserved bits, etc.).</p><div class="quotebox"><cite>Denis wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>2. I think the client should NOT try again after three tries ... 3. add an error-id to the error packet</p></div></blockquote></div><p>+1. error codes --&gt; obviating three retries.</p><div class="quotebox"><cite>Olaf wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>The BEP advices exponential back-off to be used.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>+1 (already in BEP)</p><br /><div class="quotebox"><cite>denis wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>4...completed downloads also in the announce response...</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Not as clearly motivated as the other changes, and why only the completes?&#160; If you intend to allocate resources between swarms based on tracker scrapes then number of seeds and downloaders would be quite useful, and if you need these values to decide which swarm to join then you don&#039;t want to conflate the announce and the scrape.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
