					<div class="postmsg">
						<div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>I&#039;m not sure it&#039;s necessary to have an error code as well.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Hmmm... There is wide variation in how people write error messages.&#160; A standardized error code is more precise and less fragile: error messages might change from release to release and between implementations.&#160; Standardized error codes enable automated response.&#160; Standardized error codes also allow humans to recognize the same error across trackers, across clients, and across web searches for related information. </p><p>Those are broad generalizations, but usually correct.&#160; So we should start the conversation with &quot;there should be error codes&quot; and then convince us that there shouldn&#039;t be.</p>
