				<div class="postright">
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>BitTorrent uses UDP for DHT, LSD, and UDP tracking.</p><p>I assume you refer to UDP for file transport.&#160; BitTorrent DNA uses UDP, and it is being introduced into uTorrent.&#160; It not only improves NAT traversal but allows us the freedom to change the congestion controller.... DNA uses a &quot;less than best-effort&quot; congestion controller so that BitTorrent acts as a background file transfer mechanism.</p><p>We are working out how to use UDP as a canary to backoff BitTorrent TCP connections when talking to legacy peers.</p>
